POLAND DAYBOOK: Polimex, PGE Earnings; Inflation Expectations

-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-02-28T06:40:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/poland-daybook-polimex-pge-earnings-inflation-expectations.html
Polimex SA, Poland’s second-largest
builder, said fourth-quarter net income rose to 52.7 million
zloty ($18 million), compared with the 44.1 million-zloty mean
estimate in a Bloomberg survey.  Net income at PGE SA fell to 3.01 billion zloty, the
largest Polish power utility said in a preliminary report.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
* The central bank publishes inflation expectations at 10 a.m.
* Polimex holds a news conference on earnings at 10 a.m.
* The financial regulator holds a news conference at 10 a.m.
*  Zaklady Azotowe Pulawy SA  holds a news conference on earnings
at 11 a.m.
* The  Finance Ministry  publishes the results of its Treasury
bill auction at 12 p.m.  EQUITY MOVERS:
*  KGHM Polska Miedz SA , Poland’s only copper producer, will
propose paying 30 percent to 50 percent of 2010 profit as a
dividend, Chief Executive Officer Herbert Wirth told the Parkiet
newspaper.
*  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA , Poland’s dominant
gas company, may reverse some writedowns, increasing fourth-
quarter operating profit, Parkiet reported.
* Zaklady Azotowe Pulawy SA, Poland’s largest fertilizer
producer, posted October-December net income of 17.1 million
zloty, compared with a loss of 15 million zloty a year earlier.  MARKETS:
* The benchmark WIG20 stock index rose 0.7 percent to 2,673.52
* The MSCI Emerging Markets Index rose 0.2 percent at 7:36 a.m.
* The zloty strengthened to 3.9746 to the euro from 3.9799.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino in Warsaw 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  